# Task

Extend derive(BamlType) to also implement ToBamlValue for structs and enums.

## File to Modify
`baml-bridge/crates/baml-bridge-derive/src/lib.rs`

## CRITICAL: Must Mirror BamlValueConvert Exactly

The generated ToBamlValue impl must produce BamlValue structures that round-trip through BamlValueConvert. Study the existing from-direction code carefully.

### For Structs
```rust
// BamlValueConvert expects: BamlValue::Class(name, field_map)
// where field_map uses RUST FIELD NAMES (not aliases)
fn to_baml_value(&self) -> BamlValue {
    let mut fields = BamlMap::new();
    fields.insert("field1".to_string(), self.field1.to_baml_value());
    fields.insert("field2".to_string(), self.field2.to_baml_value());
    // ... all fields, including None for Option::None
    BamlValue::Class(Self::type_name().to_string(), fields)
}
```

### For Unit Enums
```rust
// BamlValueConvert expects: BamlValue::Enum(enum_name, variant_string)
fn to_baml_value(&self) -> BamlValue {
    let variant = match self {
        Self::Variant1 => "Variant1",
        Self::Variant2 => "Variant2",
    };
    BamlValue::Enum(Self::type_name().to_string(), variant.to_string())
}
```

### For Data Enums (Tagged Unions)
```rust
// Same as struct variant - BamlValue::Class with tag field
fn to_baml_value(&self) -> BamlValue {
    match self {
        Self::Text { content } => {
            let mut fields = BamlMap::new();
            fields.insert("type".to_string(), BamlValue::String("Text".into()));
            fields.insert("content".to_string(), content.to_baml_value());
            BamlValue::Class(Self::type_name().to_string(), fields)
        }
        // ...
    }
}
```

## Field Ordering and Inclusion Rules

1. **Field names**: Use Rust names, NOT aliases (aliases are for LLM prompts only)
2. **All fields included**: Even Option::None fields must be in the map as BamlValue::Null
3. **Preserve order**: Use IndexMap/BamlMap to preserve field declaration order
4. **Nested types**: Recursively call .to_baml_value() on each field

## Testing Strategy (Round-Trip Property Tests)

```rust
use proptest::prelude::*;

proptest! {
    #[test]
    fn round_trip_struct(value in arb_my_struct()) {
        let baml_val = value.to_baml_value();
        let recovered = MyStruct::try_from_baml_value(baml_val)?;
        prop_assert_eq!(value, recovered);
    }
}
```

## Acceptance Criteria
1. ToBamlValue generated alongside BamlValueConvert in derive macro
2. Struct fields use Rust names (not aliases)
3. Option::None produces BamlValue::Null
4. Round-trip tests pass: value -> to_baml_value -> try_from_baml_value -> equal
